==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Littorina
<hw>Lit"to*ri"na</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL. See
<er>Littoral</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A genus of small
pectinibranch mollusks, having thick spiral shells, abundant between
tides on nearly all rocky seacoasts. They feed on seaweeds. The common
periwinkle is a well-known example. See <er>Periwinkle</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Littress</ent>⟦br⟧
